## Task Start Ritual (Do This Every Time)

The script `scripts/op_context.py` fetches everything Claude needs automatically:
your task details, the parent feature, and all sibling tasks with their statuses.

### Step 1 — Run the context fetcher

```bash
# Prints full context + ready-to-paste prompt
python scripts/op_context.py 40

# Also copies the prompt block to clipboard
python scripts/op_context.py 40 --copy

# Saves to .claude_context (Claude Code reads this file automatically if present)
python scripts/op_context.py 40 --file
```

The output shows you:
- Your task: requirements, acceptance criteria, assignee, Work/Spent time
- Parent feature: business context, budget
- Sibling tasks IN PROGRESS by other developers (coordinate before coding)
- Already completed sibling tasks (what has been built — don't duplicate)
- Pending sibling tasks (don't implement their scope yet)
- A ready-to-paste Claude Code prompt at the bottom

### Step 2 — Open VS Code in the project repo

```bash
code /path/to/OPintegration
```

### Step 3 — Paste the generated prompt into Claude Code

Copy the block between the "PASTE THIS INTO CLAUDE CODE" lines.
Claude will confirm the plan before writing any code.

### Setup (one-time per developer machine)

```bash
# 1. Generate personal API token:
#    OpenProject > Avatar > My Account > Access Tokens > + API access token

# 2. Store YOUR token in GCP Secret Manager:
gcloud config set project opintegr
gcloud secrets create op-api-token-yourname --replication-policy="automatic"
echo -n "YOUR_TOKEN" | gcloud secrets versions add op-api-token-yourname --data-file=-

# 3. Set env vars (add to ~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc):
export OP_DEVELOPER="yourname"

# 4. Auth for Secret Manager access:
gcloud auth application-default login --project opintegr
```

Each developer has their own secret: `op-api-token-{firstname}`.
When someone leaves, their OP account is blocked and the token dies automatically.

